DOE initiated the current rulemaking on June 2, 2008, by publishing on its Web site its âRulemaking Framework for Residential Central Air Conditioners and Heat Pumps.â (A PDF of the framework document is available at 
http://www1.eere.energy.gov/buildings/appliance_standards/residential/cac_heatpumps_new_rulemaking.html.
) DOE also published a notice announcing the availability of the framework document and a public meeting on the document, and requesting public comment on the matters raised in the document. 73 FR 32243 (June 6, 2008). The framework document described the procedural and analytical approaches that DOE anticipated using to evaluate energy conservation standards for central air conditioners and heat pumps and identified various issues to be resolved in conducting this rulemaking.

